subject: Swimming
lead_paragraph: Natalie Coughlin of the United States won the 100-meter butterfly and Randall Bal won the 100 backstroke at the FINA short-course World Cup super final in Belo Horizonte, Brazil. Coughlin won in 56.39 seconds, nearly matching her tournament record of 56.34 set in 2002.
